# GitHub Essental Commands

- git init :
initialize and track the current working direcotry

- git status : 
check the status of the git directory (changes to be made/commits etc)

- git add :
add a commit to be changed

- git commit :
commit changes to files in the repo

git commit -a to add and commit at once

- git diff :
show differences for files/branches before/after commits 

- git rm {file} :
remove file

- .gitignore :
Files to be ignored for commiting 
For files to be escaped from this rule, add a ! before the file/path

- git branch :
Branch into a new parallel repository
-d - delete a branch 

- git checkout / git switch :
Cd into this new repository

- git log :
log and summary
git log --graph --all --oneline (concise verison)

- git merge :
merge one repository with another 

- git tag :
give names to specific points in the history of our project



